Gianni Infantino (2-L), the president of FIFA and Patrice Motsepe (R) president of the Confederation of African Football (CAF) arrive at the 43th edition general assembly on March 12, 2021, in the Moroccan capital Rabat. FADEL SENNA / AFP JOHANNESBURG - Patrice Motsepe is the new president of the Confederation of African Football (CAF). Motsepe is calling for unity as he faces enormous challenges in the federation. He was unanimously elected at the 43rd General Assembly in Morocco, Rabat. READ: WATCH: Patrice Motsepe unveils manifesto for CAF presidency The 56-year-old will succeed Malagasy Ahmad Ahmad, who's serving a two-year ban. Dr Patrice Motsepe has been elected new CAF President
